The paper deals with the problem of comparing and analyzing graph-based topological summaries, specifically merge trees, which are commonly used in data analysis and scientific visualization. This suggests that the paper may belong to the computer graphics (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), graphics (cs.GR), or social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
